# 3-scale_up

## Application server vs Web server â€” Scale Up Infrastructure

In this task, we upgrade the previous infrastructure by adding a new load-balancer and splitting the existing components (web server, application server, and database) into dedicated servers. This improves scalability, performance, and availability.

---

## Infrastructure Components

### 1. New Load Balancer (HAProxy)
**Why added:**  
To create a load-balancer cluster with the original one. This removes the load balancer as a single point of failure.

**Role:**  
Distributes traffic to backend web servers. Ensures high availability.

---

### 2. Dedicated Web Server (Nginx)
**Why added:**  
Separating static content serving from application logic increases performance and makes scaling easier.

**Role:**  
Serves static
